name: CustomBot Workshop

venue.name: Melbourne Connect Rooms M02/M03
venue.address:
Superfloor, Melbourne Connect
700 Swanston St, Carlton VIC 3053

bleachedEventDetails:
This workshop will be presented by experienced facilitator and teacher David Ebert and the world renowned RoboCup Junior Victoria CustomBot Crew. In this Workshops, we will be delving into the world of building robots using Arduino & Raspberry Pi, and answering all the questions you have about these exciting technologies. 

This workshop will commence at 9am, and conclude by 3pm.

This Workshop is primarily designed for mentor attendees (teachers, coaches and others facilitating students engaging in RoboCup Junior), however mentors are welcome to bring along 2-3 students to also participate in the workshop

Please note this workshop is not catered - feel free to bring along your own food/drink or purchase from the onsite cafe during the morning tea and lunch breaks. 

Places are also limited - if you register and are subsequently unable to make it, please unregister yourself or let us know ASAP so the place is still available.

Additionally, please complete the pre-workshop survey at the following link when you register for the workshop so we can make sure you get the most out of the session: https://forms.microsoft.com/r/mzyPLcvbc7

name: Introduction to Robotics Workshop

venue.name: Melbourne Connect Rooms M13/M14
venue.address:
Superfloor, Melbourne Connect
700 Swanston St, Carlton VIC 3053

bleachedEventDetails:
This workshop will cover the basics of robotics, programming and engineering design, using LEGO® Education SPIKE™ Prime, including:
  • Learn how to use SPIKE™ Prime in your classroom
  • Prepare to teach STEAM using the SPIKE™ Prime lesson units
  • Develop ideas for facilitating hands-on lessons
  • Share classroom management tips
  • Learn the basics for participating in RoboCup Junior Events
This workshop will be presented by experienced facilitator and teacher David Ebert, with support from other RoboCup Junior Committee Members. This workshop will commence at 9am, and conclude by 3pm. This Workshop is primarily designed for mentor attendees (teachers, coaches and others facilitating students engaging in RoboCup Junior), however mentors are welcome to bring along 2-3 students to also participate in the workshop Participants who do not have a Spike Prime kit will be able to use a provided kit on the day, however please email us in advance that you will need a kit so we can make sure enough are available. name: Custom Bot Workshop & Creator Space Tour
bleachedEventDetails:
This is not a Challenge specific workshop, but the topics will include Developing Robots Using the Raspberry Pi Pico Microcontroller and  Using a Raspberry Pi Single Board Computer (e.g. for vision sensing). These topics are widely applicable across all divisions.
 
This workshop will be presented by experienced facilitator and teacher David Ebert, with support from other RoboCup Junior Committee Members. This workshop will commence at 9am and conclude by 3pm, including a tour of the The Creator Space at The University of Melbourne. Please bring along your laptop and robot (if you have one). This workshop is primarily designed for mentor attendees (teachers, coaches and others facilitating students engaging in RoboCup Junior), however mentors are welcome to register 2-3 students to also participate in the workshop. Students must be accompanied by a mentor. Participants who do not have a custom robot, please email us in advance so that we can provide a Ro/Box custom robot kit (https://robox.com.au/). These will be available for $35 payable on the day. Please note this workshop is not catered - feel free to bring along your own food/drink or purchase from the onsite cafe during the morning tea and lunch breaks. Places are also limited - if you register and are subsequently unable to make it, please unregister yourself or let us know ASAP so the place can be made available to others.
Please note: this will be a hands-on workshop, but for safety reasons will not include any soldering.
